features: Mini Portable 60% Layout Keyboard: T68SE is a 68-key mechanical keyboard, compact size, adding separate arrow keys and "Del" keys, saving space while providing you with all the functions of a normal keyboard Type-C connection also provides more stable transmission.

Clicky Blue Switch: Blue switch clicks when pressed and has excellent tactile feedback, it is the most authentic, original and unique mechanical switch with a long life span, providing accurate tactile feedback for gaming and typing.

Full Anti-Ghosting: T68SE 68 keys gaming keyboard all keys conflict-free, can be triggered at the same time, which makes the game and typing more effective and smooth, also can be easily achieved through the auxiliary key Fn full-size keyboard.

Classic Blue LED Backlight：The T68se mechanical keyboard offers a variety of static and dynamic lighting effects with bright and vivid colors. You can switch between 19 built-in lighting modes and adjust the brightness and speed of the lighting using dedicated keys.

Compatibility and After-sales Guarantee: Suitable for Windows 11/10/8/7/XP, Vista and Linux (Mac OS partially compatible), your satisfaction and happiness will be our motivation and direction to pursue continuous product upgrade, if you encounter any problems, please feel free to contact us.

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Can I take out the switches and replace it with another switch? The switch of the T68SE keyboard is soldered, so you cannot remove it to replace it with a different switch. Is a 68-key keyboard considered a 60% or 65% keyboard? The 68-key keyboard is a 65% keyboard, which includes arrow keys, page up/down keys, as well as delete and home keys. Can it adjust the light color? The T68SE keyboard cannot change the keyboard light color, but you have 19 different lighting modes to choose from.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Impressive Compact Keyboard with Stellar Performance
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I recently purchased the DIERYA T68SE Wired 60% Mechanical Gaming Keyboard in white, and I must say, it has exceeded my expectations. This keyboard combines the convenience of a compact layout with the exceptional performance of mechanical switches, making it a standout choice for both gaming and office use.First and foremost, the build quality of this keyboard is outstanding. The compact 68-key layout not only saves precious desk space, but it also feels solid and durable. The sleek white design with LED backlighting adds a touch of elegance and enhances the overall aesthetic of my setup. The keyboard is also accompanied by a convenient stand-alone arrow/control key cluster, allowing for easy navigation and efficiency.The highlight of the DIERYA T68SE is undoubtedly its clicky blue mechanical switches. They deliver a satisfying tactile feedback with an audible click, making each keystroke a delight. The actuation force is just right, providing a pleasant typing experience for extended periods. Whether I'm typing up documents or engaging in intense gaming sessions, the responsiveness and accuracy of the switches are remarkable.The LED backlighting is another commendable feature. The vibrant and customizable lighting effects add a visually pleasing element to the keyboard. The ability to adjust brightness and choose from various lighting modes allows for personalization, matching my mood or gaming environment effortlessly.Setting up the keyboard was a breeze. It is compatible with Windows, Mac, and Linux, so I had no issues connecting it to my Windows laptop. The included USB cable is of good quality and ensures a reliable connection.One minor drawback I encountered is the lack of dedicated media control keys. Although it doesn't hinder the overall functionality of the keyboard, having dedicated media keys would have been a nice addition for convenience.In conclusion, the DIERYA T68SE Wired 60% Mechanical Gaming Keyboard is an impressive peripheral that offers a blend of functionality, performance, and style. Its compact form factor, clicky blue switches, and customizable LED backlighting make it an excellent choice for gamers and professionals alike. Despite the absence of dedicated media keys, this keyboard deserves a solid five-star rating for its exceptional performance and value for money.

reviews.reviewText: Good keyboard for the price. This is my travel keyboard so that I don't have to use a laptop keyboard while I'm in hotel rooms. For that it works well and is very cost effective.
